# RFC-020 Spec — Catálogo dinámico de agentes desde OpenCode
## Delta specs for change "rfc20-fix-agents"

## 1. Requirements

### 1.1 Functional

| ID | Requirement | Priority |
|----|------------|----------|
| F01 | `listAgents?()` method on `OpenCodeSessionAdapter` interface returning `Result<AgentCatalogResult>` | P0 |
| F02 | HTTP adapter: `POST /opencode/agents` returns `{ agents: [{ id, label? }] }`. Cache with TTL 30s. On failure → degraded with cache or `{ ok: false }`. | P0 |
| F03 | CLI adapter: `opencode agents` CLI command → parse stdout line-by-line. Cache TTL 30s. | P0 |
| F04 | PTY adapter: delegate to `opencode agents` CLI (same as CLI). Cache TTL 30s with `pty:` prefix. | P0 |
| F05 | `listSupportedAgents()` in use-cases.ts returns `{ agents: readonly string[], degraded?: { reason: string } }`. Contract signature changes. | P0 |
| F06 | `setActiveAgent()` validates agent against dynamic catalog (not just `isSupportedAgent()`). Falls back to `FALLBACK_AGENTS` if catalog unavailable. | P0 |
| F07 | `isSupportedAgent()` remains as validation against `FALLBACK_AGENTS` for config/defaults usage only. | P1 |
| F08 | `FALLBACK_AGENTS = ["build", "plan", "gentleman", "sdd-orchestrator"]` replaces `SUPPORTED_AGENTS` as the hardcoded safety net. | P0 |
