## 5. Implementation Notes

### 5.1 Cache strategy

- Same `Map<string, CacheEntry>` pattern as `ModelCatalogCache` in session adapter.
- Cache key format: `agent::{chatId}::{projectId ?? "-"}::{sessionId ?? "-"}`
- TTL: `AGENT_CATALOG_CACHE_TTL_MS = 30_000`
- On failure: serve cache if exists + still fresh; else return `{ ok: false }` with `degraded`
- On failure without cache: return `{ ok: false, agents: [], degraded: { reason, usingCache: false } }`

### 5.2 `listSupportedAgents()` in use-cases.ts

```ts
async listSupportedAgents(chatId: string): Promise<{
  agents: readonly string[];
  degraded?: { reason: string };
}> {
  if (!deps.adapter.listAgents) {
    logger.warn("[agent-catalog] Adapter does not support listAgents — using FALLBACK_AGENTS");
    return { agents: FALLBACK_AGENTS, degraded: { reason: "unsupported" } };
  }

  const catalog = await deps.adapter.listAgents({ chatId });
  if (!catalog.ok) {
    logger.warn("[agent-catalog] Adapter error — using FALLBACK_AGENTS", {
      error: catalog.error.message,
    });
    return { agents: FALLBACK_AGENTS, degraded: { reason: "adapter-error" } };
  }

  if (!catalog.value.ok) {
    logger.warn("[agent-catalog] Catalog degraded — using FALLBACK_AGENTS", {
      reason: catalog.value.degraded?.reason ?? "unknown",
      usingCache: catalog.value.degraded?.usingCache ?? false,
    });
    return { agents: FALLBACK_AGENTS, degraded: { reason: catalog.value.degraded?.reason ?? "unknown" } };
  }

  return { agents: catalog.value.agents.map((a) => a.id) };
}
```

### 5.3 `setActiveAgent()` validation change

After `isSupportedAgent()` check (or replacing it), fetch dynamic catalog:

```ts
// In setActiveAgent():
const agent = normalizeAgentSelectionInput(input.agent);

// Step 1: check fallback list (fast-path for common agents)
if (!FALLBACK_AGENTS.includes(agent)) {
  // Step 2: check dynamic catalog for unknown agents
  const { agents, degraded } = await this.listSupportedAgents(input.chatId);
  if (!agents.includes(agent)) {
    return errResult(ERROR_CODES.VALIDATION_ERROR, "Agente no válido");
  }
}
```

Note: `FALLBACK_AGENTS` used as fast-path to avoid unnecessary network call for common agents. Full catalog check only for agents not in fallback list.

### 5.4 Logger fallback calls

Every fallback must call:
```ts
logger.warn("[agent-catalog] Fallback triggered: {reason} - using FALLBACK_AGENTS", {
  reason: "timeout" | "unavailable" | "unsupported" | "unknown",
  usingCache: boolean,
});
```

